---

<PageLayout title='About' {headings} comment>
  <p>Hi! I'm an indie developer based in Shenzhen, China.</p>
  <p>Stoic Digital Craftsman (Guitarist / Developer / Designer)</p>
  <p>
    Building creative tools like <a href='https://github.com/LIUBINfighter/Obsidian-Tab-Flow'
      >Tab Flow for Obsidian</a
    >. Exploring AI, music, and the art of productive leisure (Otium).
  </p>

  <h2 id='story'>Here's the story</h2>
  <p>
    Jay Bridge is an undergraduate in SUSTech, driven by a desire to live a free and peaceful life.
    After a time spent in robotics and physics competitions, he decided to build something cool and
    useful in his workspace, and gradually fell in love with the design philosophy of Obsidian.
  </p>
  <p>
    Like many young people, Jay used to worry about freedom, wealth, and the future. But recognizing
    personal limits and the brevity of life doesn’t confine him; it frees him to focus on what truly
    matters.
  </p>

  <blockquote>
    <p>Even if I were nothing, I could still play the guitar.</p>
    <p>即使我什么都不是，我还可以弹弹吉他。</p>
  </blockquote>

  <p>
    The guitar has been a constant companion throughout Jay's second decade of life, and it will
    likely stay with him in the third. To play favorite songs better, he started exploring ways to
    read and write guitar tabs with timing information, then expanded into plain-text score formats
    and AI-assisted conversion from static tabs to editable text.
  </p>
  <p>
    That exploration became projects like Tab Flow (Obsidian plugin) and Simple Tabify (alphaTex OCR
    model family).
  </p>

  <p>
    Looking around, even if the world is full of geniuses, Jay believes there are still things that
    only he can do.
  </p>
  <p>环视自己的周围，即使都是天才，我也有只有我才能去做的事。</p>

  <p>
    From VS Code to GitHub, Jay found the beauty of DevOps and agile development — code as design,
    and flow as a craft.
  </p>
  <p>
    Now Jay continues building Tab Flow &amp; Simple Tabify, while enjoying a life full of curiosity,
    creating, and deep work.
  </p>

  <h2 id='otium'>Jay's Otium</h2>
  <p>Guitar, Music, Obsidian, Touhou Project, Cocktail, Swimming, ASMR, AI Agents.</p>
</PageLayout>
